Sorry for the delay on this. I came down with a blinding headache on the way home from #Bears camp and needed some time to rest. Here are some of my thoughts from what I saw in Bourbonnais.

People are picking on Mitch Trubisky a lot for not being sharp enough with his throw. I am here to say it's not all on him. Receivers had a bad tendency to drop passes run poor routes and not look for the ball quick enough to make a play on it.  #Bears

That said I can say this with total confidence. Trubisky and Allen Robinson are completely on the same page. I don't think they missed a single connection all morning. Every pass Mitch threw him was on target and caught. That duo is going to produce.  #Bears

As for Trubisky himself? He still has that tendency to get lazy with his fundamentals particularly when under pressure or throwing it deep. He's excellent at the short-to-intermediate range but forgets his feet sometimes in those situations. Still something to work on. #Bears

Javon Wims has not taken his foot off the gas in practice. Though he didn't make a lot of catches that was because the QBs weren't throwing it to him. He was open quite a bit. Though known mostly for his size he's actually faster than he looks. #Bears

The #Bears running backs are so much more dangerous in the passing game now. Tarik Cohen is obviously a threat but both David Montgomery and Mike Davis had nice plays in pass-catching drills. That dimension of the offense is about to pop wide open.

Adam Shaheen returned for practice but was limited in reps probably to be careful with his back issue. He did have a nice play in red zone drills with a TD over Deon Bush. Still the tight ends did not make any significant impact plays especially with Trey Burton out.  #Bears

Khalil Mack makes it look way too easy. Every time he stepped on the field for a rep he created havoc. Bobby Massie had a nightmare blocking him. On one play Mack got into the backfield so fast that Chase Daniel basically just gave up and ate the sack. Beast.  #Bears

The surprise player who stood out to me was Joel Iyiegbuniwe. The second-year ILB is bigger now and hasn't lost any of his speed and quickness. Running backs could not block him in pass protection drills. Danny Trevathan is still the clear cut starter but Iggy is rising. #Bears

Throwing against that #Bears secondary is going to be torture for quarterbacks. Kyle Fuller and Prince Amukamara were all over WRs in drills creating turnovers. Eddie Jackson was on the prowl and Ha Ha Clinton-Dix had his first INT of camp. Everywhere you throw is ill-advised.

Elliott Fry responded to Eddy Pineiro's strong Thursday practice with a near-flawless Friday. Both #Bears kickers have looked more than capable of being the starter on this team. Their battle will likely be decided in live game action during the preseason.
